news.title: RBI's pandemic rate cuts give the biggest stimulus to realty
news.para: On average, the repo rate stayed at 4%, but loans for commercial real estate averaged around 7.14% at the end of February 2022. Likewise, housing loans also saw rates drop by 129 basis points.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Five developers siphon off Rs 6 crore in housing scam
news.para: The complaint was filed on Tuesday against the developers and three others including a manager of a financial firm in Mumbai.

news.title: CMDA can approve all multi-storey buildings now; files needn't go to Tamil Nadu govt
news.para: The existing regulation to submit the planning permission applications to the government has been done away with. It will expedite approval process for multi storied building.

news.title: Bihar RERA introduces conciliation forum
news.para: The real estate regulatory body has set up Bihar RERA Conciliation and Dispute Resolution Cell (BCDRC) to facilitate amicable conciliation of disputes between promoters and allottees through dispute settlement forum or cell.

news.title: JSW taps Carlyle to back bid for Holcim's Indian cement operations
news.para: Holcim Group, the world's largest cement maker, is looking to exit India 17 years after its entry, putting its twin listed arms - Ambuja Cement and ACC Ltd - up for sale as part of a global strategy to focus on core markets.

news.title: HDFC to sell 10% stake in HDFC Capital to ADIA for Rs 184 crore
news.para: Set up in 2016, HDFC Capital is the investment manager to HDFC Capital Affordable Real Estate Funds 1, 2 and 3; and is aligned with the government's goal to increase housing supply and support the Pradhan MantriAwas Yojana - 'Housing for All' initiative, HDFC Ltd said in a statement.

news.title: SC seeks ED's reply on steps taken to bring back Unitech's buyer's money stashed in Cyprus
news.para: ​The top court also appointed former Supreme Court Judge AM Sapre to look into the policy and finalization of standard operating procedure for monetization of project land assets and non-project land assets of Unitech.

news.title: Hosur in Tamil Nadu to get industrial township and airport
news.para: A new SIPCOT industrial park, an industrial housing township and airport has been proposed in Krishnagiri district, which includes Hosur. The development comes in the backdrop of Hosur emerging as one of the largest industrial growth centres in the state.

news.title: SpaceMantra looks to become unicorn company in the next two years
news.para: Currently we have 400 users on our platform. We have tied up with 300-400 original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and have over 50,000 listed products. Every day we are adding 5,000 new products or SKUs, said Anoop Kumar Mittal, founder of SpaceMantra.

news.title: Nagpur: Over 10,000 trees to be felled on ceiling lands for commercial gains
news.para: The parcels of lands where tree felling is proposed for commercial gains have breeding populations of tigers and other Schedule I to IV animals — leopards, sloth bears, four-horned antelope, sambars, spotted deer, wild boars, and nilgais — listed under the Wildlife Protection Act (WPA), 1972.

news.title: Revenue of paint companies to grow 10-12% this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: Demand from residential real estate projects, which accounts for ~30% of decorative paints, will outpace growth in the repainting segment (~70% of decorative paint revenue) this fiscal.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body offers early bird incentives to developers
news.para: In a circular, the town planning department announced no interest for those who pay their full fees by June 30 after paying the initial 10% of development permission fee.

news.title: As status turns to freehold, Chandigarh housing board finds property buyers
news.para: The board managed to sell five, including one residential (freehold) and four commercial (freehold), units in the e-tender of vacant dwelling units, earning a revenue of Rs 3.67 crore.

news.title: Supertech insolvency: Lender asks better settlement plan, 'definite upfront payment' of dues
news.para: On March 25, the Delhi bench of the NCLT had directed to initiate insolvency proceedings against Supertech Ltd over a petition filed by the Union Bank of India for non-payment of dues worth around Rs 432 crore.

news.title: Property tax services restored in Vijayawada
news.para: CDMA responded to the story and opened all property and vacant land tax related services from Monday evening.
